  "texts": [
    "The non-censored observations are ordered first and each observation conditions on its M closest predecessors that are also non-censored.",
    "This construction enables evaluation of the (approximated) data likelihood in a single pass over the data, given parameters α, τ 2, and Θ, without the need for a latent process and with matrix inversions of size at most M ×M.",
    "This results in a highly scalable inference scheme for censored Bayesian SVC models.",
    "Following the MCMC sampling procedures described previously, we obtain L posterior samples (α, Θ, τ 2, w) for Full Latent model and Latent Vecchia, and (α, Θ, τ 2) for Latent-Free Vecchia model.",
